The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Shimla, Feb. 11 (PTI): Flooded with complaints of husbands and close male relatives interfering in the functioning of panchayats headed by women, the Himachal Pradesh government has issued a directive to officials not to entertain orders from unauthorised persons and warned the women pradhans of action, including expulsion.

 panchayat pradhans count for more than a third (about 40 per cent) of the 3243 panchayats in the state.

 Panaji (PTI): The government is scanning 15 land deals involving foreign-partnered companies mostly Russian to check Foreign Exchange Management Act (Fema) violations. This follows concerns raised by central agencies regarding the deals.

 New Delhi (PTI): Two Maharashtra police officers, arrested on charges of being part of Abdul Karim Telgis stamp paper racket, have been granted bail by the Supreme Court. Sub-inspectors Dattatray Krishnaji Ghule and Hitendera Manohar Vichar were arrested in October 2004 for foisting cases against Telgis rivals.

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has slapped a fine of Rs 15,000 on a lawyer for using forged documents to prepare a loan agreement between two parties in 1997, after taking suo motu cognisance for contempt of court against him.

 Bhilwara (PTI): Five inmates of Bhilwara Central Jail fled on Sunday morning after removing rods and jumping over a high wall, an official said. Four were undertrials, while the fifth was serving a life term. A jail guard has been suspended.

 Jammu (PTI): A Siberian crane was shot dead and two others were injured on Saturday in Jammu districts Gharana wetland reserve near the border with Pakistan, officials said. The injured cranes have been taken to Manda sanctuary.




